data.value:
Daisy was brought to the shelter by the police after they had trapped her from the street. Daisy is a very friendly girl. She is highly intelligent and likes to be busy, although she is just as happy to have attention and cuddles, her favourite being belly rubs. She will fall to the floor and roll over for a tummy tickle.
She is more dominant character, bust has gotten on well with other dogs. She has been introduced to - both adults and young pups. She walks well on the leash, and gets long with all people she has met.
She is a very affectionate girl. She is untested ith cats. Having been with us for long, and been so overlooked, it would be amazing for her to get her chance.
